# Branch: main. Bumped 2026-05-14 from e7fd85b to land the NLR
# detector case (d) — PLA*N at block start + branching tail.
# Closes the HandleSelectionCursor-shape class: leaf-ish functions
# whose body has `PLA PLA` at the START of a block (eating the
# immediate parent's return address) followed by stateless logic
# and a CondBranch/Goto/fall-through that all reach RTS. Cases
# (a/b/c) only matched PLA*N immediately preceding the terminator,
# so this shape escaped recognition and the function exited with
# +2 stack drift that accumulated per call.
#   f9f48a5  v2: NLR detector case (d) — PLA*N at block start +
#            branching tail. Canonical case: SMW $00:9AEA
#            HandleSelectionCursor.CheckMovement. Detection count
#            on SMW: 4 new variant sites at 2 unique PCs —
#            $00:9AEA HandleMenuCursor (M1X1 + M0X1 + aliases)
#            and $00:EFFF RunPlayerBlockCode_00EFE8_ReturnsTwice.
#            Verified live end-to-end on SMW: user pressed Start
#            once at title → menu advanced title → 1P/2P →
#            file-select MARIO A/B/C → save selected → Yoshi's
#            Island intro → playable level → overworld reached
#            (overworld has separate visual corruption —
#            downstream bug). Attract-demo soak clean to frame
#            8124. v2 tests 162/165 unchanged.
#
