# Bumped 2026-05-03 from c3ea87e to land cfg `tail_call:<addr>`
# directive in the v2 emit pipeline. Encodes the real ROM idiom of a
# routine with its own callable entry that deliberately falls through
# into a separately-declared sibling fn (two entry points sharing a
# body). Boundary edge emits `return SiblingFn_M{m}X{x}(cpu);`
# instead of unresolvable-goto trap. Sibling-name resolution happens
# in emit_bank with a hard error on missing sibling for typo-safety.
